content: Which chemical element has the symbol Fe and atomic number 26?

Iron has the symbol Fe and atomic number 26. The name iron comes from the Old English word "iren," and its Latin name is "ferrum," which is where the chemical symbol Fe originates. Iron is a metal that is widely used in construction and manufacturing due to its strength and durability. It is also an essential element in the human body, as it is a key component of hemoglobin, the protein in red blood cells that carries oxygen throughout the body.
